# Dog Sitting Website Practice

## Goals
- Build a friendly, modern, responsive marketing site for a dog sitting company.
- Keep the site simple and easy to extend; prioritize clarity over cleverness.
- Get this site working end-to-end and deployed so anyone can access from web browser
- Spend as little money as possible (free would be great if that's an option)

## Defaults
- Use plain HTML/CSS/JS unless the user asks for a framework.
- Use semantic HTML and accessible components (labels, aria when needed).
- Browser-first layout; keep sections modular and reusable.
- Avoid heavy dependencies unless requested.
- When substantial backend is needed, use Python + FastAPI.

## Content Structure (Single Page)
- Hero: name, tagline, primary CTA.
- Services: 3-4 core service cards.
- Pricing: 2-3 tiers with brief notes.
- About: short company story and values.
- Testimonials: 2-3 short quotes.
- Contact: form + direct contact info + hours.

## Style
- Warm palette and dog-friendly tone.
- Consistent spacing scale and typography.


